{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17647376","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17647376"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:43:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:43:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18245"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18245","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18245"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.19,0.27,0.23,0.15,0.15]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10959"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81753"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10959","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10959"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18245"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67044"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4899"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7418"},{"type":"tags","id":"7422"},{"type":"tags","id":"11460"},{"type":"tags","id":"11461"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25468"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25471"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81753","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/81753"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following structures is the posterior attachment of the hip joint capsule?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Gluteal tuberosity","Greater trochanter","Intertrochanteric crest","Lesser trochanter","Linea aspera"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe hip joint capsule is a strong ligamentous structure that envelops the hip joint and provides essential stability. At its proximal end, it attaches to the acetabulum of the pelvis. The posterior aspect of the capsule attaches distally to the \u003Cstrong\u003Eintertrochanteric crest\u003C/strong\u003E, which is a prominent ridge connecting the greater and lesser trochanters on the posterior femur.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other anatomical landmarks are not sites of hip capsule attachment:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Egluteal tuberosity\u003C/strong\u003E serves as an attachment point for gluteal muscles on the posterior femoral surface\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Egreater trochanter\u003C/strong\u003E projects laterally from the femur and provides attachment for hip abductor muscles\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elesser trochanter\u003C/strong\u003E is a medial projection that serves as an attachment point for the iliopsoas muscle\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elinea aspera\u003C/strong\u003E is a longitudinal ridge on the posterior femoral shaft that provides muscle attachments\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The hip joint capsule attaches posteriorly to the intertrochanteric crest of the femur.","The hip joint capsule attaches proximally to the acetabulum, and distally to the femur."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2018). Textbook of Orthopaedics, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Singh, V. (2018). Textbook of Anatomy Abdomen and Lower Limb; Volume II (Vol. 2). Elsevier Health Sciences","Cantrell AJ, Imonugo O, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Leg Bones. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537024/","Raftery A. General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System. Ann R Coll Surg Engl. 2006 Jul;88(4):425. doi: 10.1308/003588406X114802d. PMCID: PMC1964629"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67044"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18245"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67044","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/67044"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-26T20:56:14+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-26T20:57:02+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10959"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81753"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4899","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4899"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Anatomy","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-13T17:52: